msgid "Often the configure script will try to automatically enable support for optional components based upon installed packages. This must <placeholder-1/> be allowed to happen. For example, if a user has Perl installed but has <placeholder-2/>, packages with <placeholder-3/> Perl support must not link against Perl. This automatic detection can usually be overridden using <placeholder-4/> and <placeholder-5/> or <placeholder-6/> and <placeholder-7/> switches (but note that these don't always work <d/> make sure these are tested properly!)."
